<br>
I want to know - are we really balanced?  Is there REALLY a reason to choose a straight warrior over another tank?<br>
<br>
I need to know....<br>
<br>
Kalkoric<br>
19th Level Barbarian <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uroxiana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roxiana</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/00 9:57:49 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are we Balanced?</span><hr size=1> Paladins and shadow knights have perks and<br>
minuses, but they deviate from the pure<br>
warrior- they are not as tough, they do not<br>
do as much damage, plain and simple. <br>
They have fewer hp and often ac, they cannot<br>
dual wield, and rangers are even more limited<br>
in combat with their defense caps.<br>
The hybrid classes can hold their own, and<br>
a rogue or monk can often out damage us,<br>
but when push comes to shove and you need<br>
a basher to keep the hellbeast at bay, the<br>
front ranks will always contain warriors.<br>
Once you pass level 20 and are unleashed from<br>
the damage cap you currently have, you'll<br>
stop having doubts about your power as a<br>
warrior...<br>
-Roxiana <p><b>Roxiana Morrigan<br>
Warrior of the 42nd rank<br>
Officer of Raving Lunatics<br>
Solusek Ro<br></b>
<img src="http://www.shadowfox.com/stuff/roxthum.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukupafrostheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kupa FrostHeart</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/00 10:02:06 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.flash.net/~coop37/objects/beer.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are we Balanced?</span><hr size=1> Up to level 40... ranger, pallie, Sk, etc can do about the same job as a warrior... post 40.. it's a whole nother ball game. Nobody can stand in a fight like a warrior can. We may not deal the same damage as the monk, but we can take the beats like no other.<br>
<br>
The warrior AC makes em the best tanks and the warrior HP makes 39+ clerics love us... CH is the most mana-efficient healing available when you have a 40+ warrior, esp with some HP buffs... I am often sitting close to 3k HP with full buffs, whicvh means a cleric can heal over 2k hp with one spell if I can keep the mob on me. <p><body link="green" vlink="green"><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica" SIZE=3 COLOR="green"><P ALIGN="CENTER"><A HREF=http://www.sacredguardians.com/bios/kupa.htm>Kupa FrostHeart</a><BR></FONT><FONT FACE="Arial,Helvetica" SIZE=2 COLOR="yellow">Kupa's muscles ripple in anticipation of the flames to come...</FONT></P></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ujaramena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaramena</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/00 10:26:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are we Balanced?</span><hr size=1> I would just have to say - WHO CARES?  I personally do not care much if I am balanced with the other classes.  (do not start yelling - it is only an opinion).  I just LOVE being a warrior.  Of course I am not on a PVP and have yet to duel beyond fun &quot;guild kill each other&quot; events.  Just my 2 coppers worth.<br>
<br>
