Barbarian Warrior of 30 seasons<br>
Nameless<br>
Officer of The First Seals <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uganzo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ganzo</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://people.mw.mediaone.net/aminevich/images/smurf.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/00 11:14:02 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://people.mw.mediaone.net/aminevich/images/conc.jpg hight=150 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are we Balanced?</span><hr size=1> Warriors is most balanced class in game. At 50+ we bordering on owerpowered now. After lvl 52 no other class can come close to tankin like we do and as we move up in lvls other classes keep falling behind more, with use of disciplines we can out preform any melee class, only rogue comes close in damage he can deal but he'll need us to tank for him or he'll die. Fact is now at 54 i would prefer to have another warrior in group with me over any other melee class. Fact is that group of 2 warriors, druid, enchanter, shaman, cleric, can do anything they want in Sebilis and fight to any area fast but when same group replaced 1 warrior of lvl 53 with ranger of lvl 55 they could not do most of same things.  <p>      &nbsp &nbsp<FONT SIZE="3" COLOR="red"><b>Champion</b><br></FONT>
