<FONT COLOR="#800080"><b>Maestro of Ak'Anon</b></FONT> <br>
        <FONT COLOR="#0000FF"><b><a href="http://www.sanct.com"target="web"> <u>Sanctuary</u></a></b></FONT><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaeoshadows.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taeo Shadows</A></span><br> <b>knows that Warriors are Superior</b><br>   <font color=#FF0000>(8/9/00 11:36:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are we Balanced?</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with Ganzo.  Post 50 Warriors really come into their own, in fact they have matured into what they should have ALWAYS been in my opinion - The Masters of Battle.  I retired my Warrior about 6 months ago, but after seeing the way they perform in the higher lev Kunark zones I dusted him down and I have started playing him again. These days no tank can perform like a Warrior - sure the journey there maybe be painful, but well worth it in the end I think !<br>
